<subSubSection id="C351651EFF8AEE6EFF16FE20F4932E2B" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="key">
<key id="FFDA61A4FF8AEE6EFF16FE20F4932E2B" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<keyStep id="30BF2E30FF8AEE6EFF16FE20F4922AEB" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<paragraph id="8BF43695FF8AEE6EFF16FE20F4922ACB" blockId="24.[192,1441,456,1339]" box="[192,1441,456,475]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<keyLead id="30BA95A0FF8AEE6EFF16FE20F4922ACB" box="[192,1441,456,475]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
1. Pronotal dual punctation dense and almost uniformly scattered throughout (
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF8AEE6EFB1FFE20F4022ACB" box="[1225,1329,456,475]" captionStart="Figure 99-108" captionStartId="40.[192,280,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[266,1327,199,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-76@40.[261,1365,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 99-108. Gonaphodioides skelleyi, new species (San Juan Chamula env., Chiapas, Mexico). 99) Epipharynx. 100-101) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 102-103) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). Gonaphodiopsis deloyai, new species (Cueva de Tasalolpan, Cuetzalan del Progreso, Puebla, Mexico). 104) Epipharynx. 105-106) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 107-108) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174240" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174240/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 105</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF8AEE6EFAEBFE20F4592ACB" box="[1341,1386,456,475]" captionStart="Figure 109-119" captionStartId="41.[192,279,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,216,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-87@41.[264,1368,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 109-119. Gonaphodiopsis hypogea, new species (Salamander Cave, Rancho del Cielo, Gomes Farias, Tamaulipas, Mexico). 109) Epipharynx. 110-111) Habitus (length ideogram and morphological details). 112- 113) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). Gonaphodiopsis montesdeocai, new species (Xuatusco env., Parada de los Pinos, Veracruz, Mexico). 114) Epipharynx. 115-116) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 117) Right labial palp (dorsal view). 118-119) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174242" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174242/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">115</figureCitation>
) .. 
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF8AEE6EFA44FE20F4922ACB" bold="true" box="[1426,1441,456,475]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">2</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF43695FF8AEE6EFF16FE00F4922AEB" blockId="24.[192,1441,456,1339]" box="[192,1441,488,507]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<keyLead id="30BA95A0FF8AEE6EFF16FE00F4922AEB" box="[192,1441,488,507]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
— Pronotal dual punctation sparse and rather irregularly scattered (
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF8AEE6EFB9EFE00F59E2AEB" box="[1096,1197,488,507]" captionStart="Figure 109-119" captionStartId="41.[192,279,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,216,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-87@41.[264,1368,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 109-119. Gonaphodiopsis hypogea, new species (Salamander Cave, Rancho del Cielo, Gomes Farias, Tamaulipas, Mexico). 109) Epipharynx. 110-111) Habitus (length ideogram and morphological details). 112- 113) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). Gonaphodiopsis montesdeocai, new species (Xuatusco env., Parada de los Pinos, Veracruz, Mexico). 114) Epipharynx. 115-116) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 117) Right labial palp (dorsal view). 118-119) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174242" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174242/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 111</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF8AEE6EFB6FFE00F4102AEB" box="[1209,1315,488,507]" captionStart="Figure 120-129" captionStartId="42.[192,278,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[270,1289,192,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-76@42.[267,1371,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 120-129. Gonaphodiopsis pachecoi, new species (Rancho Nuevo, San Cristobal de las Casas, Chiapas, Mexico). 120) Epipharynx. 121-122) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 123-124) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). Gonaphodiopsis teopiscaensis, new species (4 mi. NW Teopisca, Chiapas, Mexico). 125) Epipharynx. 126-127) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 128-129) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174244/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">122, 126</figureCitation>
) ............ 
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF8AEE6EFA44FE00F4922AEB" bold="true" box="[1426,1441,488,507]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">3</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30BF2E30FF8AEE6EFF16FDC0F49329EB" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<paragraph id="8BF43695FF8AEE6EFF16FDC0F493298B" blockId="24.[192,1441,456,1339]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<keyLead id="30BA95A0FF8AEE6EFF16FDC0F493298B" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
2(1). Elytra elongate, feebly widened posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF8AEE6EFCCBFDC0F2B1292B" box="[797,898,552,571]" captionStart="Figure 99-108" captionStartId="40.[192,280,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[266,1327,199,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-76@40.[261,1365,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 99-108. Gonaphodioides skelleyi, new species (San Juan Chamula env., Chiapas, Mexico). 99) Epipharynx. 100-101) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 102-103) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). Gonaphodiopsis deloyai, new species (Cueva de Tasalolpan, Cuetzalan del Progreso, Puebla, Mexico). 104) Epipharynx. 105-106) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 107-108) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174240" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174240/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
); interstriae feebly convex on disc, somewhat more convex on preapical declivity. Reddish brown, pronotum and elytra shadowy darker on disc. Length 4.0-4.5 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="F35C7605FF8AEE6EFD89FD80F38B296B" box="[607,696,616,635]" name="Mexico" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="498FF877FF8AEE6EFD1EFD80F218296B" box="[712,811,616,635]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498FF877FF8AEE6EFCE0FD80F2A1296B" box="[822,914,616,635]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Puebla</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498FF877FF8AEE6EFC4BFD80F555296B" box="[925,1126,616,635]" country="Mexico" name="San Luis Potosi" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">San Luis Potosí</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498FF877FF8AEE6EFBA7FD80F438296B" box="[1137,1291,616,635]" country="Mexico" name="Tamaulipas" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Tamaulipas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498FF877FF8AEE6EFAC1FD80F4B9296B" box="[1303,1418,616,635]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
) 
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF8AEE6EFEFEFD60F5DE298B" box="[296,1261,648,667]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
............................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B4D16FF8AEE6EFBB6FD60F5DE298B" authority="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Gordon, 2012" authorityName="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Gordon" authorityYear="2012" box="[1120,1261,648,667]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gonaphodiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deloyai" status="new species">
