</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20C57FCFF8AEE6EFB20FD60F493298B" box="[1270,1440,648,667]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF43695FF8AEE6EFF16FD40F49329EB" blockId="24.[192,1441,456,1339]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<keyLead id="30BA95A0FF8AEE6EFF16FD40F49329EB" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
— Elytra short, distinctly broadened posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF8AEE6EFCEAFD40F2AC29AB" box="[828,927,680,699]" captionStart="Figure 109-119" captionStartId="41.[192,279,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,216,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-87@41.[264,1368,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 109-119. Gonaphodiopsis hypogea, new species (Salamander Cave, Rancho del Cielo, Gomes Farias, Tamaulipas, Mexico). 109) Epipharynx. 110-111) Habitus (length ideogram and morphological details). 112- 113) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). Gonaphodiopsis montesdeocai, new species (Xuatusco env., Parada de los Pinos, Veracruz, Mexico). 114) Epipharynx. 115-116) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 117) Right labial palp (dorsal view). 118-119) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174242" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174242/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
); interstriae convex on disc, subcariniform on preapical declivity. Chestnut brown or piceous. Length 3.5-4.5 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="F35C7605FF8AEE6EFB40FD20F5DC29CB" box="[1174,1263,712,731]" name="Mexico" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="498FF877FF8AEE6EFB28FD20F44129CB" box="[1278,1394,712,731]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
) ... 
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF8AEE6EFEFEFD00F5C329EB" box="[296,1264,744,763]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
.................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B4D16FF8AEE6EFBDCFD00F5C329EB" authority="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Gordon, 2012" authorityName="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Gordon" authorityYear="2012" box="[1034,1264,744,763]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gonaphodiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montesdeocai" status="new species">
